{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place onions, parsley and oil in mixing bowl, chop <b>5 sec\/speed 5<b> then sauté <b>5 min\/100°C\/speed <b>.","Add tomatoes, sugar, salt and pepper then, with simmering basket in place of measuring cup, cook <b>15 min\/100°C\/speed <b>.","Add stock cubes and 900 g boiling water then, with simmering basket in place of measuring cup, simmer <b>15 min\/98°C\/speed <b>.","Place couscous in a large serving dish and sprinkle over cinnamon. Set scales on then ladle 600 g sauce out of mixing bowl, pouring over couscous (scales will read -600 g). Place a jug on mixing bowl lid and weigh in 100 g boiling water. Remove from lid, pour water over couscous, stir with spatula, then cover with foil and set aside.","Add fish to mixing bowl then, with simmering basket in place of measuring cup, simmer <b>5-10 min\/98°C\/\/speed <b> until fish is cooked.","Fluff couscous with a fork. Remove fish pieces with a slotted spoon and arrange over couscous. Pour over a little more sauce. Scatter with almonds and parsley then serve, with remaining sauce on the side."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["240 g onions, quartered","15 g fresh parsley, plus 3 sprigs for garnish","25 g olive oil","800 g tinned chopped tomatoes (2 x 400 g tins)","1 tsp sugar","½ tsp fine sea salt","¼ tsp ground black pepper","2 fish stock cubes (for 0.5 l each)","1000 g water, boiling","300 g couscous","¼ tsp ground cinnamon","600 - 700 g fish, skinless, boneless, cut in pieces (5 cm) (e.g. hake, haddock, cod)","2 Tbsp flaked almonds, toasted"]}],"id":"r247278","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-NmQpfoDa86M\/XZQxtwAEPRI\/AAAAAAAAcx4\/t4Efq2AeOiMlI2JVNcK3ejUfvGTc3WZ1wCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_z6CvPYCwPGlOiDf8.png","title":"Trapanese Couscous with Fish, Tomatoes and Almonds - Couscous alla trapanese con pesce, pomodori e mandorle","publishedAt":"2018-05-28T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"40.5 g","fat":"15.3 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"63.5 g","calories":"2440 kJ \/ 580 kcal"},"usefulItems":"serving dish, slotted spoon, jug, aluminium foil, ladle","hintsAndTricks":["This dish is a celebration of the diversity of Sicilian cuisine, a region that has been influenced over time by the different cultures that settled there. Couscous is a traditional Moroccan grain that was brought to Italy in the 12th century. Trapani is a city in western Sicily with a traditional way of preparing fish couscous featuring almonds, which grow all over the Sicilian countryside. Together with fragrant cinnamon, they provide the perfect flavour backdrop to the tender, flaked fish."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","1h","4 portions"]}